<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup/M1: quiet 2-note RH (B4 D5), full LH 4-note G triad open voicing
- M2-3: alternating ⑤/⑥/① — short harmonic rhythm; hands track melody in parallel 3rds
- M6 (Bm D): 4-note LH open Bm (B2 F#3 D3 B3) — widest range of arrangement
- M7: V7 LH = D3 A3 C4 F#3 (complete dominant 7th in bass)
- M8: Em7 3-note RH "333" for emotional climax at "e2" peak
- M9: ⑤² 2nd inversion creates suspension heading into final phrase
- M12: ④ C major interlude — brief iv color (actually IV in major)
- M14: ①"334" = G4 B4 D5 G5 double octave — triumphant close

VOICE LEADING:
- M1→2: RH top note D5 common across G→D
- M6: Bm inner voice F# descends to E (Em) in M8 — long-range soprano line
- LH pedal tracks chord roots faithfully throughout

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light pickup → builds through M5-6 → climax Em7 M8 → sustained D in M9
- Full "334" final close with G1 pedal
-->
